  <bodyText><![CDATA[<p><strong>Finally, holidaymakers can swap their local walk for the trails of the Alps, their sofa for a sunny lakeside or pool, or their living room for the breath-taking sights of the Matterhorn. As Inghams, the tour-operator famous for their outdoor, walking, cycling and sightseeing holidays in Europe open the doors to <a data-udi="umb://document/92803bd348ec48c1b64d53e77931172d" href="/{localLink:umb://document/92803bd348ec48c1b64d53e77931172d}" title="Switzerland">Switzerland</a>—people can finally experience more this summer.</strong></p>
<p>Taking people on holiday for the first time since October 2020, the trusted tour operator have prided themselves on doing right by their customers throughout the pandemic. Continuing to put their customer’s interests first, Inghams only travel to destinations when the Foreign Common Development Office (FCDO) advises it is safe to do so. This combined with their <a data-udi="umb://document/fa72be9e45bc442089252c6a18a0d2ae" href="/{localLink:umb://document/fa72be9e45bc442089252c6a18a0d2ae}" title="In Safe Hands">covid-19 refund policy</a> and the safety measures they’ve put in place, continues to offer people that extra peace of mind when booking a holiday with the tour operator.<br /><br />Now, knowing they’re in safe hands, their guests will be able to travel to many ‘experience more’ destinations in Switzerland from 31st July 2021 onwards.<br /><br /><a data-udi="umb://document/02a5945a51fe4587bf5aa72b66298bea" href="/{localLink:umb://document/02a5945a51fe4587bf5aa72b66298bea}" title="Switzerland Late Deals"><strong>7-nights in Switzerland this summer – from £559pp</strong></a><br /><br />Switzerland’s stunning landscapes and dramatic snow-dusted mountain peaks, tranquil shimmering lakes, and charming, picturesque towns and villages are ready when you are!</p>
<p>This summer, Inghams guests can escape to the great outdoors and experience more of what Switzerland has to offer by boat, bus, train or mountain railway, or explore the scenery on foot or bike—Inghams have a range of Swiss summer holiday destinations available including <a data-udi="umb://document/527f062dda374fee961e7ca5209c3d26" href="/{localLink:umb://document/527f062dda374fee961e7ca5209c3d26}" title="Davos">Davos</a>.<br /><br /><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/switzerland/graubunden-region/davos/solaria-apartments?accommodationNode=22378&amp;programCode=GBINB&amp;tourOpCode=ING&amp;catalogue=010&amp;obArrGateway=CHDV&amp;departurePoint=AIRPORT-LHR&amp;propertyCode=CHDV0104&amp;boardBasis=SC&amp;unitCode=A2&amp;transportType=FLT&amp;departureDate=18/09/2021&amp;duration=7&amp;adults=2&amp;children=0&amp;childages=#0">7-nights at the 3-star Solaria Apartments, Davos, Switzerland</a>. Self-catering from £559 per person flying on 18 September 2021 from London Heathrow. Based on 2 adults.</p>
<p>Inghams summer holidays are available to reserve now with deposits of just £150 per person. Flights from Birmingham, Bristol, Edinburgh, Liverpool, London and Manchester are available. For more summer 2021 holidays to Switzerland, visit <a data-udi="umb://document/02a5945a51fe4587bf5aa72b66298bea" href="/{localLink:umb://document/02a5945a51fe4587bf5aa72b66298bea}" title="Switzerland Late Deals">Inghams’ summer deals page</a>.</p>
<p><strong>-ENDS-</strong></p>
<p><strong>Inghams’ Company Information</strong></p>
<p>Inghams was founded by Walter Ingham in 1934, born out of his enduring passion for ski, mountaineering and walking.</p>
<p>Today, Inghams offers ski holidays in the winter to 77 resorts in 8 countries, plus winter wonderland and Santa Breaks to Lapland, with flights from 15 UK regional airports. It also has a popular Summer Experiences holiday programme to many European destinations and Canada, and a dedicated Self-guided and Escorted Tours programme.</p>
<p><strong>Contact details: Jenny Nicholls, PR Manager</strong><br /><strong>jenny.nicholls@hotelplan.co.uk 07773205464</strong></p>]]></bodyText>
